value.value: A P2Y receptor that is a translation product of the human P2RY1 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof. The preferred ligand is ADP.
A P2Y receptor that is a translation product of the human P2RY12 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof. The preferred ligand is ADP.
A P2Y receptor that is a translation product of the human P2RY13 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof. The preferred ligand is ADP.
A P2Y receptor that is a translation product of the human P2RY14 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof. The preferred ligand is UDP-glucose.
A P2Y receptor that is a translation product of the human P2RY2 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof. The preferred ligands are ATP and UTP.
A P2Y receptor that is a translation product of the human P2RY4 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof. The preferred ligand is UTP.
A P2Y receptor that is a translation product of the human P2RY6 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof. The preferred ligand is UDP.
An adenosine receptor protein that is a translation product of the human ADORA1 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.
An adenosine receptor protein that is a translation product of the human ADORA2A gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.
An adenosine receptor protein that is a translation product of the human ADORA2B gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.
An adenosine receptor protein that is a translation product of the human ADORA3 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.
An opioid receptor protein that is a translation product of the human OPRD1 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof. The preferred ligands are enkephalins.

An N-formyl peptide receptor that is a translation product of the human FPR1 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof. The preferred ligand is the peptide fMet-Leu-Phe, a bacterial peptide that acts as a chemoattractant in various pathophysiological conditions.
A glycoprotein hormone receptor that is a translation product of the human FSHR gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof. The preferred ligand is follitropin (follicle-stimulating hormone).

A free fatty acid receptor that is a translation product of the human FFAR1 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof. Its preferred ligands are medium and long-chain fatty acids. It potentiates fatty acid-stimulated insulin secretion in pancreatic islets.
A free fatty acid receptor that is a translation product of the human FFAR2 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof. It mediates stimulation of adipogenesis by short-chain fatty acids.
A free fatty acid receptor that is a translation product of the human FFAR3 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof. It mediates stimulation of leptin release by short-chain fatty acids.
A galanin receptor that is a translation product of the human GALR1 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.
A galanin receptor that is a translation product of the human GALR2 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.
A galanin receptor that is a translation product of the human GALR3 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.
A gonadotropin-releasing hormone receptor that is a translation product of the human GNRHR gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof. The preferred ligand is gonadotropin-releasing hormone I.
A gonadotropin-releasing hormone receptor that is a translation product of the human GNRHR2 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof. The preferred ligand is gonadotropin-releasing hormone II.
An opioid receptor protein that is a translation product of the human OPRK1 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof. The preferred ligand is dynorphin.
A leucine-rich repeat-containing G-protein coupled receptor 4/5/6 that is a translation product of the human LGR4 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.
A leucine-rich repeat-containing G-protein coupled receptor 4/5/6 that is a translation product of the human LGR5 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.
A leucine-rich repeat-containing G-protein coupled receptor 4/5/6 that is a translation product of the human LGR6 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.
A leukotriene B4 receptor that is a translation product of the human LTB4R gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.
A leukotriene B4 receptor that is a translation product of the human LTB4R2 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.

A glycoprotein hormone receptor that is a translation product of the human LHCGR gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof. The preferred ligands are lutropin (luteinizing hormone) and choriogonadotropin (choriogonadotropic hormone).
A lysophospholipid (LPA) receptor that is a translation product of the human LPAR4 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.
A Mas-related G-protein coupled receptor that is a translation product of the mouse Mrgpra1-Mrgpra8 genes, 1:1 orthologs thereof, or a semi-ortholog thereof.

definition.value: Category=family. Note: This gene is present as a single copy in rat and has undergone a lineage-specific expansion in mouse. Orthology with human is not clear; possibly human MRGPRX1-MRGPRX4 genes represent an orthologous independent lineage-specific expansion.

value.value: A Mas-related G-protein coupled receptor that is a translation product of the mouse Mrgprb1, Mrgprb2, Mrgprb3, Mrgprb4, Mrgprb5, Mrgprb8, or Mrgprx2 genes, or 1:1 orthologs thereof. These genes belong to a small subfamily, found in the rodent lineage, that also includes several pseudogenes.

label.value: rodent-type Mas-related G-protein coupled receptor X1

value.value: A Mas-related G-protein coupled receptor that is a translation product of the mouse Mrgprx1 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof. RF-amide-related peptides are reported to be the preferred ligands.

definition.value: Category=gene. Note: The rat ortholog is called SNSR1. Although commonly designated as orthologous to human MRGPRX1, these genes are not as closely related as one would expect of true orthologs.

value.value: A Mas-related G-protein coupled receptor that is a translation product of the human MRGPRD gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof. It is reported to bind beta-alanine.
A Mas-related G-protein coupled receptor that is a translation product of the human MRGPRE gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.
A Mas-related G-protein coupled receptor that is a translation product of the human MRGPRF gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.
A Mas-related G-protein coupled receptor that is a translation product of the human MRGPRG gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.
A Mas-related G-protein coupled receptor that is a translation product of the mouse Mrgprh gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.
A Mas-related G-protein coupled receptor that is a translation product of the human MAS1L gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.

A Mas-related G-protein coupled receptor that is a translation product of the human MRGPRX1, MRGPRX2, MRGPRX3 or MRGPRX4 genes, 1:1 orthologs thereof, or a semi-ortholog thereof. These genes belong to a small subfamily, found in the primate lineage, that also includes several pseudogenes.
A melatonin receptor that is a translation product of the human MTNR1A gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof. The preferred ligand is melatonin.
A melatonin receptor that is a translation product of the human MTNR1B gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof. The preferred ligand is melatonin.
An MT1-like melatonin receptor that is a translation product of the human GPR50 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.
An opioid receptor protein that is a translation product of the human OPRM1 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof. The preferred ligands are beta-endorphin and enkephalins.

A muscarinic acetylcholine receptor that is a translation product of the human CHRM1 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof. This receptor mediates slow excitatory postsynaptic potential in the postganglionic nerve and is also expressed in exocrine glands and in the central nervous system.

A muscarinic acetylcholine receptor that is a translation product of the human CHRM2 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof. This receptor is expressed in cardiac tissues and acts to slow the heart rate to normal after sympathetic nervous system stimulation.

A muscarinic acetylcholine receptor that is a translation product of the human CHRM3 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof. This receptor is expressed in many glands, in lungs, and in the smooth muscles of blood vessels.
A muscarinic acetylcholine receptor that is a translation product of the human CHRM4 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof. This receptor is expressed in the central nervous system.
A muscarinic acetylcholine receptor that is a translation product of the human CHRM5 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof. Its expression pattern is yet to be elucidated.
A neuromedin-U receptor that is a translation product of the human NMUR1 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof. This receptor is expressed predominantly in peripheral tissues.
